    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from jupyterthemes import jtplot\n",
    "\n",
    "jtplot.style(context=\"notebook\", fscale=1, grid=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "from astromodels import Powerlaw, Exponential_cutoff, Constant, Band\n",
    "from astromodels.utils.configuration import astromodels_config\n",
    "astromodels_config.modeling.ignore_parameter_bounds = True\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.modeling.new_astromodels import SBPL\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.data.gbm_data import GBMData\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.geometry.gbm_geometry import GBMGeometryPosHist\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.response.gbm_response import GBMResponseGenerator\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.response.response_precalculation import ResponsePrecalculation\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.response.src_response import EarthResponse, CGBResponse, GalacticCenterResponse, PointSourceResponse\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.modeling.source import PhotonSourceFixed, SAASource, NormOnlySource\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.modeling.functions import AstromodelFunctionVector\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.modeling.model import ModelDet\n",
    "\n",
    "from gbmbkgpy.io.plotting.plot import plot_lightcurve"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "a19167fe",
   "metadata": {},

    "## DATA"
   ]
  },

   "id": "ca5a746d",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:01:17.416185Z",

    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# get daily GBM data\n",
    "gbmdata = GBMData(name=\"gbmn0\", \n",
    "                date=\"200510\", \n",
    "                data_type=\"ctime\", \n",
    "                detector=\"n6\", \n",
    "                echans=[\"1\",\"2\",\"3-5\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rebin the data to 20 second bins\n",
    "gbmdata.rebin_data(min_bin_width=20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b8198cee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## GEOMETRY"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "962e8151",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:01:19.224236Z",

     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:01:20.207578Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# init geometry object for Fermi/GBM at the given date\n",
    "geom = GBMGeometryPosHist(date=\"200510\")"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "050e74ac",
   "metadata": {},

    "# General response Generator\n",
    "drm_gen1 = GBMResponseGenerator(geometry=geom, det=\"n6\", Ebins_in_edge=np.geomspace(10,2000, 101), data=gbmdata)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Response precalculation for extended sources\n",
    "rsp_pre1 = ResponsePrecalculation(drm_gen1, Ngrid=10000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "993d9b2e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Responses for extended sources"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5338e7a6",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:01.966739Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:01.966131Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:22.504498Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:22.503752Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Time where to calculate the effective responses - linear interpolation in between\n",
    "interp_time = np.linspace(gbmdata.time_bins[0,0], gbmdata.time_bins[-1,-1], 800)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Galactic Center\n",
    "gc_rsp = GalacticCenterResponse(geometry=geom, interp_times=interp_time, resp_prec=rsp_pre1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Earth Albedo\n",
    "earth_rsp = EarthResponse(geometry=geom, interp_times=interp_time, resp_prec=rsp_pre1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# CGB\n",
    "cgb_rsp = CGBResponse(geometry=geom, interp_times=interp_time, resp_prec=rsp_pre1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c848e3e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Response for point source"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "8943472b",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:22.508566Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:22.508078Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.283408Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.282699Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Response for Crab\n",
    "crab_rsp = PointSourceResponse(response_generator=drm_gen1, interp_times=interp_time, ra=83.633, dec=22.015)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7238d00a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Modelling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0fdf6c0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Photon sources\n",
    "\n",
    "We use [astromodels](https://github.com/threeML/astromodels) to define the spectra and combine this with the precalculated responses for the different sources."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "877d8172",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.288053Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.287338Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.489439Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.488719Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A point source\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define spectrum\n",
    "pl_crab = Powerlaw()\n",
    "pl_crab.K.value = 9.7\n",
    "pl_crab.index.value = -2.1\n",
    "\n",
    "# define source\n",
    "crab = PhotonSourceFixed(\"Crab\", pl_crab, crab_rsp)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# extended sources\n",
    "\n",
    "#EARTH\n",
    "earth_spec = SBPL()\n",
    "earth_spec.K.value = 0.015\n",
    "earth_spec.alpha.value = -5\n",
    "earth_spec.beta.value = 1.72\n",
    "earth_spec.xb.value = 33.7\n",
    "\n",
    "earth = PhotonSourceFixed(\"Earth\", earth_spec, earth_rsp)\n",
    "\n",
    "#CGB\n",
    "cgb_spec = SBPL()\n",
    "cgb_spec.K.value = 0.11\n",
    "cgb_spec.alpha.value = 1.32\n",
    "cgb_spec.beta.value = 2.88\n",
    "cgb_spec.xb.value = 30.0\n",
    "cgb = PhotonSourceFixed(\"CGB\", cgb_spec, cgb_rsp)\n",
    "\n",
    "#GC\n",
    "pl1_gc = Powerlaw()\n",
    "pl1_gc.K.value = 0.08737610581967094\n",
    "pl1_gc.index.value = -1.45\n",
    "\n",
    "pl2_gc = Powerlaw()\n",
    "pl2_gc.K.value = 252.3829377920772\n",
    "pl2_gc.index.value = -2.9\n",
    "\n",
    "exp_gc = Exponential_cutoff()\n",
    "exp_gc.K.value = 0.1036025649336684\n",
    "exp_gc.xc.value = 8\n",
    "\n",
    "total = pl1_gc+pl2_gc+exp_gc\n",
    "\n",
    "gc = PhotonSourceFixed(\"GC\", total, gc_rsp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "578cd99f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### SAA\n",
    "\n",
    "The de-excitation after an SAA transit is modelled as a simple exponential decay. But it is different for different energy channels and we have no info how to combine these. Therefore every energy channel gets an independent SAA Decay assigned."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "52748e32",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.493431Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.492760Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.498152Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.497534Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "exp_decay = Exponential_cutoff()\n",
    "exp_decay.K.value = 1000\n",
    "exp_decay.xc.value = 5000\n",
    "afv_saa = AstromodelFunctionVector(gbmdata.num_echan, base_function=exp_decay)\n",
    "\n",
    "exit_time_saa = gbmdata.mean_time[100]\n",
    "\n",
    "saa = SAASource(\"SAA\", exit_time_saa, afv_saa)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4ed6eb0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Cosmic Rays\n",
    "\n",
    "Because we don't have a response for charged particles, we can not forward fold the signal due to the incoming Cosmic Rays. We therefore rely on good tracers of the effect. For GBM for example the McIlwain L-parameter seems to be a decent tracer. The time variablity is given by this tracer and only a total normalization (per energy channel) is fitted."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "3f6497af",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.501263Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.500836Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.505122Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.504438Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "c = Constant()\n",
    "c.k.value = 100\n",
    "afv_cr = AstromodelFunctionVector(gbmdata.num_echan, base_function=c)\n",
    "\n",
    "cr = NormOnlySource(\"CR\", geom.cr_tracer, afv_cr)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "97b44d7b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "c8625f1e",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.508307Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.507719Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.649037Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-11-02T13:02:23.648261Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = ModelDet(gbmdata)\n",
    "\n",
    "model.add_source(gc)\n",
    "model.add_source(earth)\n",
    "model.add_source(cgb)\n",
    "model.add_source(crab)\n",
    "\n",
    "model.add_source(saa)\n",
    "model.add_source(cr)"
   ]
  },
